    <div class="wrapper">
        <div class="header header-filter" style="background-image: url('../../assets/img/city.jpg');">
            <div class="container" ng-controller="AppController" id="home">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <h1 class="title">Realistic Random Records</h1>
                        <h2>API service for randomly generated user fields, utilizing real-world historical weighted values</h2>
                        <br />
                        <button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" ng-click="getNewRecord()">New Record</button>
                        <br /><br />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6" ng-repeat="field in record">
                        <div class="card card-signup">
                            <div class="record-header header-primary text-center">
                                <h2 class="text-capitalize">{{ field.firstname }} {{ field.lastname }}</h2>
                            </div>
                            <div class="content">
                                <div class="panel-group text-center">
                                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                                        <div class="panel-heading">Address</div>
                                        <div class="panel-body text-capitalize">
                                            <div>{{ field.location.street }}, {{ field.location.city }}, {{ field.location.state }} {{ field.location.zipcode }}</div>
                                            <div>{{ field.location.latitude }}&deg;, {{ field.location.longitude }}&deg;</div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                                        <div class="panel-heading">Birth Day</div>
                                        <div class="panel-body">
                                            {{ field.dob | date: "longDate" }}
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                                        <div class="panel-heading">Phone</div>
                                        <div class="panel-body">
                                            {{ field.phone }}
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="scroll-arrow">
                        <a href="#about"><i class="material-icons">arrow_downwards</i></a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="main main-raised">
            <div class="container" id="about">
                <div class="section text-center section-landing">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                            <h2 class="title">What is Realistic Random Records?</h2>
                            <h5 class="description">Do you need fake user information for a presentation? &nbsp;mockup? &nbsp;logic or database testing? &nbsp;Does it need to be more realistic than "John Doe" or "asdf user1"? &nbsp;Do you need hundreds or thousands of data points and you don't have an unpaid intern that will do it by hand?</h5>
                            <h3 class="description">Then this is the API for you!</h3>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="features">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                                <div class="info">
                                    <div class="icon icon-info">
                                        <i class="material-icons">fingerprint</i>
                                    </div>
                                    <h4 class="info-title">Realistic</h4>
                                    <p>All of the data fields are sourced from real-world historical databases such as <a href="https://www.census.gov/en.html" target="_blank">the US Census Bureau</a> and <a href="https://www.ssa.gov/" target="_blank">the US Social Security Administration</a>, as well as follow appropriate formats, conventions, and specifications.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                                <div class="info">
                                    <div class="icon icon-success">
                                        <i class="material-icons">casino</i>
                                    </div>
                                    <h4 class="info-title">Random</h4>
                                    <p>We use a weighted random algorithm so the generated results reflect real life. &nbsp;Someone born in 1980 is more likely to be named Michael than Abraham, and that probability is also reflected in our results.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                                <div class="info">
                                    <div class="icon icon-danger">
                                        <i class="material-icons">disc_full</i>
                                    </div>
                                    <h4 class="info-title">Records</h4>
                                    <p>There is no music here, so why call it records? &nbsp;It is a callback to the classic computer science term: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Record_(computer_science)" target="_blank">record</a> - a basic data structure that contains fields of information. &nbsp;And who doesn't love alliteration?</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="documentation" id="documentation">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                                <h2 class="title">API Documentation</h2>
                                <h3 class="title">How to use</h3>
                                <div class="description">Just send a GET request to <a href="/api/record" target="_blank">/api/record</a> . &nbsp;The results will be returned in JSON.</div>
                                <h3 class="title">Optional Query Parameters</h3>
                                <h4 class="title">&iquest;Mas Por Favor?</h4>
                                <div class="description">The default results return only a single record. &nbsp;Simply attach the quanitity parameter (?qty=n) to receive up to a max of 3000 records. &nbsp;It should look something like <a href="/api/record?qty=5" target="_blank">/api/record?qty=5</a></div>
                                <h4 class="title">Are there any other options?</h4>
                                <div class="description">Winter is Com*cough*cough*. &nbsp;Sorry. &nbsp;More features coming soon.</div>
                                <h3 class="title">Anything else I should know?</h3>
                                <div class="description">Yeah. &nbsp;The source code can be found at <a href="https://github.com/Jdothager/RandomRecords" target="_blank">Github</a>. &nbsp;Also, credit to <a href="http://presentation.creative-tim.com" target="_blank">Creative Tim</a> for the Bootstrap theme! &nbsp;Disclaimer: &nbsp;Any resemblance to actual persons, living or dead, is purely coincidental.</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
